radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits, no pleural or pericardial effusion. Liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation, small hyperdensity likely a perfusion defect or hemangioma, mild periportal edema. Normal pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands. Normal kidneys with no lesions or hydronephrosis. The colon and rectum are normal. Dilation of the appendix consistent with acute appendicitis. There is a 3.9 cm anterior uterine wall lesion, likely fibroid. No lymphadenopathy or vascular abnormalities.
